body:
@rmetzger Thank you for your review. Just pushed, I hope I've addressed your last comments with the last commit.

For the documentation, I added a bit more stuff, apart from the threading model, that I thought was also good to have: 1) enabling checkpointing, mostly borrowed from the Kafka documentation, and 2) information on how the consumer internally uses the Kinesis APIs so that users can make sense of any limit warnings they are getting in the logs.

Please let me know if there's anything else to address!

@fhueske the failure of CI build is relevant with `testJoinWithDisjunctivePred` in `JoinITCase`. The case is :
`val joinT = ds1.join(ds2).filter('a === 'd && ('b === 'e || 'b === 'e - 10)).select('c, 'g)`. 
I still don't quite understand why this case running failed after some debug work. And when i changed the filter condition with `('a === 'd && ('b === 'e || 'b === 'h - 10))` (or replace with `'d` `'f`), it can work sucessfully without exception.
